{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2017}} {{Use Indian English|date=June 2017}} {{Infobox event |title=Unnao dead bodies row |image= |caption= |date=14 January 2015 |place=[[River Ganges]], [[Unnao district]], [[Uttar Pradesh]] |coordinates = {{coord|26.617997|N|80.284111|E|type:event_region:IN|display=inline,title}} |cause=Unknown |casualties1=110 dead }}
{{Location map | India | width = 250 | float = | border = | caption = Location of the discovery in India | alt = | relief = | AlternativeMap = | overlay_image = | label = Ganga Ghat Shuklaganj balu ghat | label_size = | position = | background = | mark = | marksize = | link = | lat_deg = 26.617997 | lon_deg = 80.284111 }}
{{Location map | Uttar Pradesh | width =250 | float = | border = | caption = Location of the discovery within Uttar Pradesh | alt = | relief = | AlternativeMap = | overlay_image = | label = Ganga Ghat Shuklaganj balu ghat | label_size = | position = | background = | mark = | marksize = | link = | lat_deg = 26.617997 | lon_deg = 80.284111 }} On 14 January 2015, more than one hundred unidentified dead bodies were found floating in the [[River Ganges]] in [[Unnao district]] in the Indian state of [[Uttar Pradesh]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/india/report-unidentified-corpses-send-up-government-in-a-tizzy-2052594|title=Unidentified corpses send UP government in a tizzy|publisher=dnaindia.com|accessdate=2015-01-15}}</ref> The dead bodies are believed to be of mostly unmarried girls and children. They were later buried at the riverbank.<ref name="Unnao row">{{cite web|url=http://www.timesofindia.com/india/100-bodies-recovered-from-Ganga-Centre-seeks-info-from-UP-govt/articleshow/45888140.cms|title=100 bodies recovered from Ganga|work=Times of India|accessdate=2015-01-15}}</ref>
==Incident== The bodies, which were mostly of children and unmarried girls, were first noticed on 14 January 2015 by some villagers at [[Ganga Ghat Shuklaganj balu ghat]] in Unnao district when crows and dogs were feeding on them. The area was cordoned off by officials and 104 dead bodies were retrieved from the river. Samples were taken for forensic [[DNA profiling]], as, according to officials, postmortem was not possible. Without going for cremation the dead bodies were buried at the riverbank. On the same day, six more dead bodies were found floating in the river and retrieved from the neighbouring district of [[Jhansi]].<ref name="Unnao row"/>
One of the explanations given by the officials was that since the river had changed its course due to the construction of a new [[barrage (dam)|barrage]], the water level became lower and the bodies surfaced. A magisterial enquiry was ordered by the then Chief Minister of Uttar Pradesh [[Akhilesh Yadav]] to uncover the facts of the incident.<ref name="Unnao row"/> The chairperson of [[Bahujan Samaj Party]], [[Mayawati]], demanded [[Central Bureau of Investigation|CBI]] enquiry into the incident and said that it "has infused fear among people".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.samacharplus.com/index.php/en/cities/36-up-uttarakhand/lucknow/1628-mayawati-demands-cbi-probe-into-unnao-dead-bodies-issue|title=Mayawati demands CBI probe into Unnao dead bodies issue|publisher=Samacharplus.com|accessdate=2015-01-15}}</ref> [[Azam Khan (politician)|Azam Khan]], a cabinet minister in Uttar Pradesh government, has accused [[Sakshi Maharaj]] of being responsible for the incident; {{quote|I have come to know that Sakshi Maharaj brought a truck loaded with bodies to the spot and unloaded it into the river to defame the state government.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.timesofindia.com/india/Sakshi-Maharaj-threw-bodies-into-Ganga-Azam-Khan/articleshow/45904995.cms|title=Sakshi Maharaj threw bodies into Ganga-Azam Khan|work=Times of India|accessdate=2015-01-17}}</ref>}}
==Location== The dead bodies were found floating in a canal at [[Ganga Ghat Shuklaganj balu ghat]], which connects to the Ganges and is 60&nbsp;km southwest from [[Lucknow]], the state capital of Uttar Pradesh and 30&nbsp;km northeast from [[Kanpur]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ndtv.com/topic/unnao|title=Unnoa|publisher=ndtv.com|accessdate=2015-01-15}}</ref>
==River== The Ganges River is regarded as a holy river by Hindus and many crematory [[ghats]] are on its banks. Police officials of Unnao have offered an explanation that the bodies were of "people who were dumped in the river or buried on the banks after their families could not afford a proper cremation."
